    "## Why These Models Are Differentiable"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Maslov-Gibbs Einsum (MGE) / Thermodynamic Tensor Contraction (TTC)\n",
    "\n",
    "Both models replace discrete threshold logic with **soft sigmoid transitions**:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Discrete:  if (x > threshold): output = 1 else output = 0  [NO GRADIENT]\n",
    "Soft:      output = sigmoid(β·(x - threshold))             [SMOOTH GRADIENT]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The parameter **β** (inverse temperature) controls the sharpness:\n",
    "- **β = 1**: Fuzzy transition (smooth gradients, explores safely)\n",
    "- **β = 100**: Sharp transition (approximates discrete threshold)\n",
    "- **β-annealing**: Start fuzzy → gradually sharpen during optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the **Maslov-Gibbs bridge**: connecting discrete economics to continuous differentiable programming."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
